 same\nisoelectronic sequence cover not only a wide range of ionization parameter, but\nalso a wide range of density. On the other hand, within the same isonuclear\nsequence, less ionized ions probe lower density and smaller ionization\nparameter. Finally, we re-analyzed the high-resolution grating spectra of NGC\n5548 observed with Chandra in January 2002, using a set of PION components to\naccount for the ionized outflow. We derive lower (or upper) limits of plasma\ndensity in five out of six PION components, based on the presence (or absence)\nof the metastable absorption lines.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 29 Jul 2017 19:51:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Aug 2017 08:12:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-22"}
